#: of numpy.lib.npyio.NpzFile:46
msgid ""
"Maximum allowed size of the header.  Large headers may not be safe to load "
"securely and thus require explicitly passing a larger value. See :py:func:"
"`ast.literal_eval()` for details. This option is ignored when `allow_pickle` "
"is passed.  In that case the file is by definition trusted and the limit is "
"unnecessary."
msgstr ""

